## Phase 2: Copy Template Files [AUTO]

1. Update `package.json`:
   - Remove all Gatsby-related fields: `dependencies`, `resolutions`, `remarkConfig`, `packageManager`.
   - Replace `scripts` with the template scripts from [dev-docs-template/package.json](https://github.com/AdobeDocs/dev-docs-template/blob/main/package.json).
   - Replace `devDependencies` with the template devDependencies. Only keep extra devDependencies from the original repo if the repo specifically requires them.
   - **Do not add, remove, or change the `.gitignore` file in this phase.**
2. Download and replace workflow files in `.github/workflows/`:
   - `build-auto-generated-files.yml` from `https://raw.githubusercontent.com/AdobeDocs/dev-docs-template/main/.github/workflows/build-auto-generated-files.yml`
     This workflow auto-generates `src/pages/contributors.json` and `src/pages/adp-site-metadata.json` on every PR via CI. These files are also generated locally by `npm run dev` at startup (via `dev.js`). They will be committed after the Local Dev Review phase verifies the site works correctly.
   - `deploy.yml` from `https://raw.githubusercontent.com/AdobeDocs/dev-docs-template/main/.github/workflows/deploy.yml`
   - `stage.yml` from `https://raw.githubusercontent.com/AdobeDocs/dev-docs-template/main/.github/workflows/stage.yml`
   - `lint.yml` from `https://raw.githubusercontent.com/AdobeDocs/dev-docs-template/main/.github/workflows/lint.yml`
   - Delete old workflows: `github-pages.yml`, `test-pull-request.yml`.
3. Run `npm install` to install new dependencies.
4. Commit Phase 2 changes — follow the **Commit Protocol**:
   - Stage:
     ```
     git add package.json \
       .github/workflows/build-auto-generated-files.yml .github/workflows/deploy.yml .github/workflows/stage.yml .github/workflows/lint.yml
     ```
     *Do not stage or modify any `.gitignore` files.*
   - Show diff, ask engineer for approval, then commit with message: `add EDS template files and update package.json`

