## Phase 4: Lint & Fix [AUTO + CHECKPOINT]

### Step 4a: Run Lint [AUTO]
Run `npm run lint`. Capture and display the output.

## CHECKPOINT D: Fix Lint Errors [MANUAL / AUTO-ASSIST]

Pause and show the lint results.

Use `AskQuestion` with options: "Try fix automatically - errors only" / "Try fix automatically - errors and metadata warnings" / "Try fix automatically - errors and warnings" / "I'll fix errors manually" / "Need help with specific errors".

### If engineer selects "Try fix automatically - errors only", "Try fix automatically - errors and metadata warnings", or "Try fix automatically - errors and warnings" [AUTO]:
Determine the fix scope based on the selected option:
- **"errors only"**: Fix only lint issues reported as **errors**.
- **"errors and metadata warnings"**: Fix all **errors**, plus **warnings** from the `check-frontmatter` rule related to missing or empty `title` and `description` fields in frontmatter. To fix these, read the `check-frontmatter` linter rule source to understand what metadata fields are required, then add missing `title` and/or `description` to each flagged file's YAML frontmatter. Derive sensible values from the page's first heading (`# ...`) for `title` and from the opening paragraph for `description`. If no suitable content exists, use the filename (converted from kebab-case to title case) for `title` and a generic description like `"Overview of {title}"`.
- **"errors and warnings"**: Fix both **errors** and all **warnings** (e.g., broken links, metadata issues).

1. For each distinct lint issue type to be fixed, read the corresponding linter rule source file from `https://github.com/AdobeDocs/adp-devsite-utils/tree/main/linters` (or the local copy at `../adp-devsite-utils/linters/` if available) to understand what the rule checks and what the fix should be. Also refer to the [Block Usage Best Practices](https://github.com/AdobeDocs/dev-docs-reference/blob/main/src/pages/getting-started/dev-docs/best-practices/index.md) for correct block syntax, markdown rules, path conventions, and replacement mappings when applying fixes.
2. Apply fixes to the affected `.md` files under `src/pages/` based on the rule logic:
   - **`no-html-comments`**: Escape HTML comments by adding `\` before `<!--` and `-->` (e.g., `<!-- comment -->` → `\<!-- comment --\>`) so the comment text remains visible on the page.
   - **`no-html-tags`**: Escape HTML tags with `\` (e.g., `<br/>` → `\<br/\>`).
   - **`no-details-html`**: Flag `<details>` HTML for manual conversion to `Details` EDS block.
   - **`internal-link-extension`**: Fix internal links to use correct extensions.
   - **`anchor-link-extension`**: Fix anchor links to use correct format.
   - **`no-angle-brackets`**: Remove or escape angle brackets around URLs.
   - **`self-close-component`**: Ensure JSX components are self-closed properly.
   - **`no-unescaped-opening-curly-braces`**: Escape `{` with `\{` when not inside code blocks.
   - **`no-code-in-table`**: Flag code blocks inside tables for engineer review.
   - **`no-br-in-tables`**: Remove `<br>` tags from tables.
   - **`no-block-in-list`**: Flag EDS blocks nested inside list items for engineer review.
   - **`big-image`**: Flag oversized images for engineer review.
   - **`no-alt-text-for-image`**: Add placeholder alt text or flag for engineer review.
   - **`check-frontmatter`**: Fix frontmatter formatting issues.
   - **`no-kebab-in-filename`**: Flag files with kebab-case names (renaming requires engineer confirmation).
   - For any other errors, read the rule source to determine the fix.
3. After applying fixes, re-run `npm run lint` and display the updated results.
4. If errors remain, report them and ask the engineer:
   Use `AskQuestion` with options: "I'll fix remaining errors manually" / "Try fix again" / "Need help".

### If engineer selects "I'll fix errors manually" [MANUAL]:
Instruct the engineer:
1. **HTML comments error**: Replace HTML comments with markdown comments, or escape HTML tags with `\` (e.g., `<br/>` becomes `\<br/\>`).
2. **Hidden table cell error**: Ask content team about inconsistent column counts.
3. Fix any other errors or broken links.
4. Reference: https://github.com/AdobeDocs/adp-devsite-utils/blob/main/README.md#linting

Use `AskQuestion` with options: "All lint issues resolved" / "Need help with specific errors".

### Step 4b: Commit Lint Fixes [AUTO]
After lint issues are resolved (either automatically or manually) — follow the **Commit Protocol**:
   - Stage:
     ```
     git add -u src/pages/
     ```
   - Show diff, ask engineer for approval, then commit with message: `resolve lint errors`

