## Phase 6: Stage Redirects [AUTO + CHECKPOINT]

### Step 6a: Add Stage Redirects [AUTO]
Run: `npx --yes github:AdobeDocs/adp-devsite-utils fastlyRedirects stage --verbose`

### Step 6b: Verify Stage Redirects [AUTO]
Run: `npm run redirectCheck:stage`
Display results.

## CHECKPOINT H: Repo Owner Stage Review [MANUAL]

Pause and instruct the engineer to:

1. Ask the repo owner to check the stage site.
2. Add to the ticket: "passed over to {owner} for verification".
3. List any outstanding issues in the ticket.

Use `AskQuestion` with options: "Owner approved stage" / "Owner found issues (will fix)" / "Waiting for owner".

---

## Phase 7: Cleanup Gatsby Files [AUTO]

Delete the following Gatsby-related files and folders (if they exist):

- `gatsby-config.js`
- `yarn.lock`
- `.yarnrc.yml`
- `.markdownlint.yml` (root level, if any)
- `.yarn/` directory
- `.github/linters/` directory
- `.github/scripts/` directory (if exists)
- `.github/dependabot.yml`
- `.github/workflows/test-pull-request.yml`
- `.github/workflows/github-pages.yml`

Replace `README.md` content with the template from:
`https://raw.githubusercontent.com/AdobeDocs/dev-docs-template/main/README.md`

Revert `.github/workflows/deploy.yml` back to the template version (undo the staging workaround from Phase 5).
Download fresh copy from: `https://raw.githubusercontent.com/AdobeDocs/dev-docs-template/main/.github/workflows/deploy.yml`

Commit the cleanup — follow the **Commit Protocol**:
   - Stage:
     ```
     git rm --ignore-unmatch gatsby-config.js yarn.lock .yarnrc.yml .markdownlint.yml .github/dependabot.yml \
       .github/workflows/test-pull-request.yml .github/workflows/github-pages.yml
     git rm -rf --ignore-unmatch .yarn/ .github/linters/ .github/scripts/
     git add README.md .github/workflows/deploy.yml
     ```
   - Show diff, ask engineer for approval, then commit with message: `cleanup Gatsby files, revert deploy.yml, and update README`

---

## CHECKPOINT I: Merge to Main [MANUAL]

Pause and instruct the engineer to:

1. Create a PR and ask a **peer** (not the code owner) to review.
2. Look out for custom workflows and notify Dawn and Pat about them.
3. Merge to main when approved, then deploy to prod (with **DeployAll** option). **Prod only looks at main branch.**

Use `AskQuestion` with options: "Merged to main" / "PR under review" / "Need help".

---

## CHECKPOINT J: Test & Wait for Prod Go Signal [MANUAL]

Pause and instruct the engineer to:

1. Test on `https://main--adp-devsite--adobedocs.aem.live/{PATH_PREFIX}`
2. **Do NOT proceed until the customer gives the go signal that pages look good.**

Use `AskQuestion` with options: "Customer approved, ready for prod" / "Still waiting for approval".

